'''Aurel Bulgariu''' (sometimes spelled '''Bulgaru'''; 13 July 1934, [[Sighișoara]] – 25 March<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sighisoara.org.ro/adp/2011/hotarari.nsf/7bc19da5efdf2be6c2256c59003667d1/f694adaada5c2d34c225781e00335126/$FILE/Ph15%20%20BULGARU%20AUREL.pdf|title=H O T A R Â R E A nr. privind atribuirea denumirii "Aurel Bulgaru" salii de sport a Gimnaziului de Stat "VictorJinga" Sighisoara|language=Romanian|accessdate=April 26, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304035331/http://sighisoara.org.ro/adp/2011/hotarari.nsf/7bc19da5efdf2be6c2256c59003667d1/f694adaada5c2d34c225781e00335126/$FILE/Ph15%20%20BULGARU%20AUREL.pdf|archive-date=2016-03-04|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> or 16 April<ref name="romanticu">{{cite web|url=http://www.romanticu.org/sighisoara-dezvelirea-placii-comemorative-pe-sala-de-sport-aurel-bulgaru/|title=Sighisoara – Dezvelirea placii comemorative pe sala de sport "Aurel Bulgaru"|language=Romanian|accessdate=May 14, 2014}}</ref> 1995) was a Romanian [[handball]] player who won two world championship gold medals. He was a backcourt player.

After playing for Flamura Roșie and Locomotiva Sighișoara (1951-1954), he transferred to [[CSA Steaua București (handball)|C.C.A. Steaua]], with which he won at least one national championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.csasteaua.ro/handbal|title=Handbal|language=Romanian|accessdate=April 26, 2014}}</ref>

He played for the Romanian national team from 1954 until 1968. After he retired as an active player, he became a coach, managing the national teams of [[Egypt national handball team|Egypt]], [[Tunisia national handball team|Tunisia]] and [[Morocco national handball team|Morocco]].

He became an [[honorary citizen]] of Sighișoara.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sighisoara.org.ro/portal/portal.nsf/AllByUNID/000016AA?OpenDocument|title=Nume şi prenume|language=Romanian|accessdate=April 26, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140601124151/http://www.sighisoara.org.ro/portal/portal.nsf/AllByUNID/000016AA?OpenDocument|archive-date=2014-06-01|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>

==Honors and awards==
*''Honored Master of Sports'' ("Maestru emerit al sportului"),1961<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frh.ro/frh/pdf/istoria_jocului/Reconstructie-Consolidare-Glorie%201946-1962.pdf|title=Istoria handbalullui romanesc|language=Romanian|accessdate=April 26, 2014}}</ref>
*a goal-getter trophy has been named in his honor<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gsp.ro/sporturi/handbal/hcm-constanta-a-primit-medaliile-de-campioni-188913.html|title=HCM Constanţa a primit medaliile de campioni|language=Romanian|accessdate=April 26, 2014}}</ref>
*an international handball youth tournament is called after him<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.insport.ro/evenimente/handbal-sighisoara-turneul-international-aurel-bulgaru-2013-juniori.html|title=Handbal, Sighisoara: Turneul International Aurel Bulgaru 2013, juniori|language=Romanian|accessdate=May 14, 2014}}</ref>
* a sports hall has been named in his honor<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sighisoara.org.ro/adp/2011/hotarari.nsf/7bc19da5efdf2be6c2256c59003667d1/f694adaada5c2d34c225781e00335126/$FILE/Ph15%20%20BULGARU%20AUREL.pdf|title=H O T A R Â R E A nr. privind atribuirea denumirii "Aurel Bulgaru" salii de sport a Gimnaziului de Stat "Victor Jinga" Sighisoara|language=Romanian|accessdate=April 26, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304035331/http://sighisoara.org.ro/adp/2011/hotarari.nsf/7bc19da5efdf2be6c2256c59003667d1/f694adaada5c2d34c225781e00335126/$FILE/Ph15%20%20BULGARU%20AUREL.pdf|archive-date=2016-03-04|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>

